options, or prepare for an upcoming interview, we encourage you to explore the resources on this website and at the Career Services office.   Career Advising:  Individual** and Walk-In Advising  Career Assessments**  Interview Preparation  Career Events:  Job Fairs, Career Fairs  Career Education:  eLearning, Workshops, Discussion Panels  Graduate School Advising  Job and Internship Opportunities (uiccareers.com)   UIC Career Services is here to support currently enrolled students and alumni through their career development and job search processes.  To maintain our employer partnerships and encourage the professional and ethical behaviors of our students and alumni, we follow the below department advising guidelines.  Please read the guidelines and contact our office if you have any questions.  * Alumni: Please visit the alumni page for more information. **Students/alumni should schedule in advance.        Learn More About Career Services           Career Services Service Overview  Handout outlining key services and resources available to students and alumni.             Career Services Introduction Video  Learn about services and resources available at Career Services.             New Student Orientation to Career Services & SEO  New to UIC?  Watch this brief video to learn what Career Services and Student Employment do.             Career Services Advising  Learn what career advising is and what services are available to students.             Student Views on Career Services  Hear UIC students describe their  experiences with Career Services.             UIC Career Fairs  Learn about UIC Career Fairs and what to expect when attending.              About    Back to main content           Hours & Location    Our Services    Contact Us    Staff Directory     Career Peer Mentors      Other Career Centers    Newsletters & Recorded Webinars    Frequently Asked Questions                  UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make a